<subSubSection id="566CFFAB25EB56973249ABA11D2B7350" pageId="0" pageNumber="4421" type="taxon discussion">
<paragraph id="EE839D3C2681158A5E1FC3382FA7BA4E" pageId="0" pageNumber="4421">Taxon discussion</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F5EC5988B5C3958EB3F0D5ACC2032072" pageId="0" pageNumber="4421">
This species resembles 
<taxonomicName id="D1A45EE57695BC4977F07C2DA79579B9" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Thelypteridaceae" genus="Thelypteris" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Thelypteris (Steiropteris) decussata" order="Polypodiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="4421" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="decussata" subGenus="Steiropteris">Thelypteris (Steiropteris) decussata</taxonomicName>
(L.) Proctor, but differs from it by the costae abaxially with dense, soft, septate hairs 1-2 mm long, costules and veins adaxially with dense, strigose hairs up to 2 mm (
<bibRefCitation id="0865388C7C34922BC2473FA4CFE2659C" author="Tryon, R. M." journalOrPublisher="Fieldiana, Botany New Series" pageId="0" pageNumber="4421" pagination="1 - 80" title="Pteridophyta of Peru. Part III. 16. Thelypteridaceae" volume="29" year="1992">Tryon et al. 1992</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
